LAURIDSEN et al. v. ALEXANDER et al.* (Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. December 20, 1926.) No. 4744. F. C. Reagan and Edwin H. Fbck, both of Seattle, Wash., for appellants. Wesley Lloyd, of Tacoma, Wash., and Geox'ge Dysart and C. D. Cunningham, both of Centraba, Wash., for appebees.

*433Before RUDKIN, Circuit Judge, and DIETRICH and KERRIGAN, District Judges.

Rehearing denied February 14, 1927.

 DIETRICH, District Judge.

In its legal aspect this case is identical with No. 4742, Katie Roberts Wilson v. Margaret Jane Robinson et al., 16 F.(2d) 431, this day decided, and for the reasons assigned in that case the decree is affirmed, as there modified.

RUDKIN, Circuit Judge, dissents, for the reason stated in Wilson v. Robinson, supra.
